    "summary": "Ir. Dick C. van Ginhoven is a self employed consultant. He worked for thirteen year as Sr. Advisor Water and Sanitation, for the 'Directoraat Generaal Internationale Samenwerking' (DGIS) of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Netherlands, when he was responsible for the formulation and implementation of the Netherlands policy with regard to drinking water and sanitation in the context of international development cooperation. Besides that he was then charged with the support to (drinking)water and sanitation programmes and initiatives of the international organisations (Worldbank, UNDP, WHO, UNICEF,  etc..). \nBefore he took up this assignment ir. Dick van Ginhoven was Head of the Developement Cooperation Section at the Netherlands Embassy in Pretoria (South Africa). \nThrough his experience as Dep. Head (political) of the Gulf States Division of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Head of the Procurement Division of DGIS and Sr. Policy Advisor Co-Financing Department of DGIS he has wide knowledge and experience with matters of foreign policy, multilateral- and bilateral development cooperation \nBefore he started his career with the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, he was for 5 years employed by UNICEF as \u2018Sr. Programme Officer Water and Sanitation\u2019 in India (New Delhi) and Vietnam (Hanoi). Before that he worked for four years in Tanzania (Dar es Salaam) as \u2018Associate Expert Public Health Engineering\u2019 and \u2018Associate Expert Urban and Rural Planning\u2019 for the United Nations Centre for Human Settlements (UNCHS / Habitat). \n\nUpon his retirement from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in April 2017, Dick van Ginhoven received the Royal Award \u2018Knight in the Order of Orange-Nassau\u2019 from his Majesty King Willem-Alexander of the Netherlands.\n\nHe currently holds the position of Secretary of the Supervisory Board of the Water Integrity Network (WIN) in Berlin.\n\nIr. Van Ginhoven graduated in 1978 as Civil Engeneer (M.Sc.) at the University of Technology in Delft, the Netherlands.",
